{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":912,"text":"My name is Katrina Spade,\nand I grew up in a medical family"},{"time":4480,"text":"where it was fairly normal to talk\nabout death and dying at the dinner table."},{"time":9080,"text":"But I didn't go into medicine\nlike so many of my family members."},{"time":12680,"text":"Instead, I went to architecture school\nto learn how to design."},{"time":17920,"text":"And while I was there,\nI began to be curious"},{"time":20320,"text":"about what would happen\nto my physical body after I died."},{"time":24440,"text":"What would my nearest\nand dearest do with me?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":27960,"text":"So if the existence\nand the fact of your own mortality"},{"time":31720,"text":"doesn't get you down,"},{"time":33440,"text":"the state of our current\nfunerary practices will."},{"time":37920,"text":"Today, almost 50 percent of Americans\nchoose conventional burial."},{"time":43600,"text":"Conventional burial begins with embalming,"},{"time":45840,"text":"where funeral staff drain bodily fluid"},{"time":48640,"text":"and replace it with a mixture\ndesigned to preserve the corpse"},{"time":52520,"text":"and give it a lifelike glow."},{"time":55440,"text":"Then, as you know,\nbodies are buried in a casket"},{"time":59000,"text":"in a concrete-lined grave"},{"time":61200,"text":"in a cemetery."},{"time":64480,"text":"All told, in US cemeteries,"},{"time":66800,"text":"we bury enough metal\nto build a Golden Gate Bridge,"},{"time":72120,"text":"enough wood to build\n1,800 single family homes,"},{"time":76040,"text":"and enough formaldehyde-laden\nembalming fluid"},{"time":78840,"text":"to fill eight Olympic-size swimming pools."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83160,"text":"In addition, cemeteries\nall over the world are reaching capacity."},{"time":87720,"text":"Turns out, it doesn't really\nmake good business sense"},{"time":90560,"text":"to sell someone\na piece of land for eternity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94120,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":96160,"text":"Whose idea was that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":97800,"text":"In some places, you can't buy a plot\nno matter how much money you have."},{"time":102680,"text":"As a result, cremation rates\nhave risen fast."},{"time":106280,"text":"In 1950, if you suggested your grandmother\nbe incinerated after she died,"},{"time":111360,"text":"you'd probably be kicked\nfrom the family deathbed."},{"time":114520,"text":"But today, almost half\nof Americans choose cremation,"},{"time":118200,"text":"citing simpler,"},{"time":120680,"text":"cheaper"},{"time":122120,"text":"and more ecological as reasons."},{"time":125720,"text":"I used to think that cremation\nwas a sustainable form of disposition,"},{"time":130520,"text":"but just think about it for a second."},{"time":132960,"text":"Cremation destroys the potential we have"},{"time":135880,"text":"to give back to the earth\nafter we've died."},{"time":139440,"text":"It uses an energy-intensive process\nto turn bodies into ash,"},{"time":143640,"text":"polluting the air\nand contributing to climate change."},{"time":147800,"text":"All told, cremations in the US"},{"time":150120,"text":"emit a staggering 600 million\npounds of carbon dioxide"},{"time":154440,"text":"into the atmosphere annually."},{"time":158080,"text":"The truly awful truth"},{"time":160440,"text":"is that the very last thing\nthat most of us will do on this earth"},{"time":165040,"text":"is poison it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171120,"text":"It's like we've created, accepted\nand death-denied our way into a status quo"},{"time":176840,"text":"that puts as much distance\nbetween ourselves and nature"},{"time":180480,"text":"as is humanly possible."},{"time":182600,"text":"Our modern funerary practices\nare designed to stave off"},{"time":185480,"text":"the natural processes\nthat happen to a body after death."},{"time":188800,"text":"In other words, they're meant\nto prevent us from decomposing."},{"time":193320,"text":"But the truth"},{"time":195160,"text":"is that nature is really,\nreally good at death."},{"time":199440,"text":"We've all seen it."},{"time":200840,"text":"When organic material dies in nature,"},{"time":203600,"text":"microbes and bacteria\nbreak it down into nutrient-rich soil,"},{"time":207360,"text":"completing the life cycle."},{"time":209800,"text":"In nature, death creates life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":216000,"text":"Back in architecture school,\nI was thinking about all this,"},{"time":220400,"text":"and I set out on a plan\nto redesign death care."},{"time":224000,"text":"Could I create a system"},{"time":226080,"text":"that was beneficial to the earth"},{"time":227960,"text":"and that used nature as a guide\nrather than something to be feared?"},{"time":232680,"text":"Something that was gentle to the planet?"},{"time":235400,"text":"That planet, after all,\nsupports our living bodies"},{"time":238120,"text":"our whole lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241160,"text":"And while I was mulling this all over"},{"time":243680,"text":"over the drawing board,"},{"time":245600,"text":"the phone rang."},{"time":247520,"text":"It was my friend Kate."},{"time":249640,"text":"She was like, \"Hey,\nhave you heard about the farmers"},{"time":253280,"text":"who are composting whole cows?\""},{"time":257360,"text":"And I was like, \"Mmmm.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":259519,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":262880,"text":"Turns out that farmers\nin agricultural institutions"},{"time":265600,"text":"have been practicing something\ncalled livestock mortality composting"},{"time":269040,"text":"for decades."},{"time":270600,"text":"Mortality composting is where\nyou take an animal high in nitrogen"},{"time":274600,"text":"and cover it with co-composting materials\nthat are high in carbon."},{"time":278400,"text":"It's an aerobic process,\nso it requires oxygen,"},{"time":281440,"text":"and it requires\nplenty of moisture as well."},{"time":284800,"text":"In the most basic setup, a cow\nis covered with a few feet of wood chips,"},{"time":289200,"text":"which are high in carbon,"},{"time":290560,"text":"and left outside for nature,\nfor breezes to provide oxygen"},{"time":294880,"text":"and rain to provide moisture."},{"time":297800,"text":"In about nine months,"},{"time":300040,"text":"all that remains\nis a nutrient-rich compost."},{"time":304040,"text":"The flesh has been decomposed entirely,"},{"time":307400,"text":"as have the bones."},{"time":310520,"text":"I know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311760,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":313280,"text":"So I would definitely\ncall myself a decomposition nerd,"},{"time":317480,"text":"but I am far, far from a scientist,"},{"time":321240,"text":"and one way you can tell this is true"},{"time":323080,"text":"is that I have often called\nthe process of composting \"magic.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":327400,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":331280,"text":"So basically, all we humans need to do"},{"time":334680,"text":"is create the right environment\nfor nature to do its job."},{"time":338040,"text":"It's like the opposite\nof antibacterial soap."},{"time":341560,"text":"Instead of fighting them,"},{"time":342840,"text":"we welcome microbes and bacteria\nin with open arms."},{"time":346840,"text":"These tiny, amazing creatures"},{"time":349600,"text":"break down molecules\ninto smaller molecules and atoms,"},{"time":353640,"text":"which are then incorporated\ninto new molecules."},{"time":358280,"text":"In other words, that cow is transformed."},{"time":362160,"text":"It's no longer a cow."},{"time":364440,"text":"It's been cycled back into nature."},{"time":367800,"text":"See? Magic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":372440,"text":"You can probably imagine\nthe light bulb that went off in my head"},{"time":375520,"text":"after I received that phone call."},{"time":377640,"text":"I began designing a system"},{"time":379440,"text":"based on the principles\nof livestock mortality composting"},{"time":383440,"text":"that would take human beings\nand transform them into soil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391840,"text":"Fast-forward five years"},{"time":393760,"text":"and the project has grown in ways\nI truly never could have imagined."},{"time":398000,"text":"We've created a scalable,\nreplicable non-profit urban model"},{"time":402480,"text":"based on the science\nof livestock mortality composting"},{"time":406000,"text":"that turns human beings into soil."},{"time":409600,"text":"We've partnered and collaborated\nwith experts in soil science,"},{"time":412960,"text":"decomposition, alternative death care,"},{"time":415520,"text":"law and architecture."},{"time":417680,"text":"We've raised funds\nfrom foundations and individuals"},{"time":420960,"text":"in order to design\na prototype of this system,"},{"time":424640,"text":"and we've heard from tens of thousands\nof people all over the world"},{"time":428440,"text":"who want this option to be available."},{"time":433080,"text":"OK."},{"time":434320,"text":"In the next few years,"},{"time":436160,"text":"it's our goal to build the first\nfull-scale human composting facility"},{"time":442080,"text":"right in the city of Seattle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":443880,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":451880,"text":"Imagine it,"},{"time":453880,"text":"part public park,"},{"time":455840,"text":"part funeral home,"},{"time":457600,"text":"part memorial to the people we love,"},{"time":460320,"text":"a place where we can reconnect\nwith the cycles of nature"},{"time":463440,"text":"and treat bodies\nwith gentleness and respect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":468640,"text":"The infrastructure is simple."},{"time":470600,"text":"Inside a vertical core,"},{"time":472240,"text":"bodies and wood chips undergo\naccelerated natural decomposition,"},{"time":476360,"text":"or composting,"},{"time":477680,"text":"and are transformed into soil."},{"time":481160,"text":"When someone dies, their body\nis taken to a human composting facility."},{"time":486480,"text":"After wrapping the deceased\nin a simple shroud,"},{"time":489280,"text":"friends and family carry the body\nto the top of the core,"},{"time":493160,"text":"which contains the natural\ndecomposition system."},{"time":498680,"text":"During a laying in ceremony,"},{"time":500560,"text":"they gently place the body into the core"},{"time":502960,"text":"and cover it with wood chips."},{"time":505360,"text":"This begins the gentle transformation\nfrom human to soil."},{"time":511000,"text":"Over the next few weeks,\nthe body decomposes naturally."},{"time":514960,"text":"Microbes and bacteria\nbreak down carbon, then protein,"},{"time":517760,"text":"to create a new substance,"},{"time":519880,"text":"a rich, earthy soil."},{"time":522640,"text":"This soil can then be used\nto grow new life."},{"time":525800,"text":"Eventually, you could be a lemon tree."}]},{"cues":[{"time":529586,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":530760,"text":"Yeah, thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":537880,"text":"Who's thinking about\nlemon meringue pie right now?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":540440,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":542600,"text":"A lemon drop?"},{"time":544720,"text":"Something stronger?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":547320,"text":"So in addition to housing the core,"},{"time":549560,"text":"these buildings will function\nto support the grieving"},{"time":552280,"text":"by providing space for memorial services\nand end-of-life planning."},{"time":556560,"text":"The potential for repurposing is huge."},{"time":559120,"text":"Old churches and industrial warehouses\ncan be converted into places"},{"time":563760,"text":"where we create soil and honor life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567800,"text":"We want to bring back the aspect of ritual"},{"time":570000,"text":"that's been diluted\nover the past hundred years"},{"time":572800,"text":"as cremation rates have risen"},{"time":574920,"text":"and religious affiliation has declined."},{"time":579440,"text":"Our Seattle facility will function\nas a model for these places"},{"time":583000,"text":"all over the world."},{"time":585120,"text":"We've heard from communities\nin South Africa, Australia,"},{"time":588280,"text":"the UK, Canada and beyond."},{"time":591960,"text":"We're creating a design toolkit"},{"time":594360,"text":"that will help others\ndesign and build facilities"},{"time":598240,"text":"that will contain technical specifications"},{"time":600840,"text":"and regulatory best practices."},{"time":603080,"text":"We want to help individuals,\norganizations,"},{"time":605600,"text":"and down the road, municipalities"},{"time":607840,"text":"design and build facilities\nin their own cities."},{"time":612040,"text":"The idea is that every one of these places\nshould look and feel completely different"},{"time":616040,"text":"with the same system inside."},{"time":617960,"text":"They're really meant to be designed\nfor the neighborhood in which they reside"},{"time":622040,"text":"and the community which they serve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":626480,"text":"The other idea is\nfor supportive staff to be on hand"},{"time":629720,"text":"to help families with the care\nand preparation of loved ones' bodies."},{"time":634520,"text":"We're banishing practices\nthat bewilder and disempower"},{"time":637960,"text":"and creating a system\nthat is beautiful and meaningful"},{"time":642320,"text":"and transparent."},{"time":645080,"text":"We believe that access\nto ecological death care"},{"time":647760,"text":"is a human right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":652640,"text":"OK, so you know the old saying,"},{"time":655760,"text":"if you can compost a cow,\nyou can compost a human?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":658360,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":663280,"text":"Turns out, it's true."},{"time":666320,"text":"Since 2014, we've been\nrunning a pilot project"},{"time":669400,"text":"in the hills of North Carolina"},{"time":671280,"text":"with the Forensic Anthropology Department\nat Western Carolina University."},{"time":676200,"text":"Six donor bodies\nhave been covered in wood chips,"},{"time":679600,"text":"oxygen provided by breezes,"},{"time":681920,"text":"microbes and bacteria doing their jobs."},{"time":685440,"text":"This pilot program has allowed us\nto demonstrate that it's possible"},{"time":688960,"text":"to harness the incredible power\nof natural decomposition"},{"time":692680,"text":"to turn human bodies into soil,"},{"time":695400,"text":"and we're working\nwith other universities as well."},{"time":698480,"text":"Soil scientists\nat Washington State University,"},{"time":702520,"text":"the grad students, anyway,"},{"time":704080,"text":"are working to compost\nteeth with amalgam fillings"},{"time":708160,"text":"so that we can understand\nwhat happens to the mercury therein."},{"time":712040,"text":"Next up, we'll be beginning experiments"},{"time":714120,"text":"to determine what happens\nto chemo drugs and pharmaceuticals"},{"time":717600,"text":"during the composting process,"},{"time":719360,"text":"and whether additional\nremediation will be needed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":725640,"text":"By the way,"},{"time":727400,"text":"composting creates a great deal of heat,"},{"time":729920,"text":"especially this particular\ntype of composting."},{"time":733880,"text":"One week after we began\ncomposting our fifth donor body,"},{"time":738680,"text":"the temperature inside\nthat mound of wood chips"},{"time":741840,"text":"reached 158 degrees Fahrenheit."},{"time":746120,"text":"Imagine harnessing that heat\nto create energy"},{"time":749160,"text":"or comfort the grieving on a cold day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":753040,"text":"The death care revolution has begun."},{"time":755720,"text":"It's an exciting time to be alive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":759640,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":760880,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}